WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:04.236
<i>Previously on</i> Greenleaf...

00:04.238 --> 00:06.338
- We cover the debt.
- You give us Triumph II.

00:06.340 --> 00:08.507
That way, the money gets replaced
and you don't go to jail.

00:08.509 --> 00:10.709
You keep your church,
and we get ours.

00:10.711 --> 00:13.645
We have the opportunity
to do something together.

00:13.647 --> 00:17.216
We copastor, build whatever
we want across the street.

00:17.218 --> 00:20.552
I don't need a copastor any more
than I need a cane to walk with.

00:20.554 --> 00:22.187
I ain't done nothing to nobody.

00:22.189 --> 00:24.023
Yeah, you did.
You hurt those girls.

00:24.025 --> 00:25.724
- You are sick!
- Stupid bitch!

00:27.461 --> 00:31.497
They didn't do anything
they didn't want to.

00:35.369 --> 00:38.070
Mac is dead. How can
this be without scandal?

00:38.072 --> 00:40.672
It was selfdefense.
Grace is a hero.

00:40.674 --> 00:43.609
And if I ask what you think, you
think it's great or you shut up.

00:43.611 --> 00:46.645
The Zora I know would never let
anyone talk sideways to her.

00:46.647 --> 00:48.113
Fine, I'll dump him.

00:48.115 --> 00:49.782
I am grateful for Robert.

00:49.784 --> 00:52.217
He wasn't always
the devil he became.

00:52.219 --> 00:56.221
Sometimes I think that Mac
became the way he was

00:56.223 --> 00:59.324
watching Daddy,
what he did to me.

01:03.264 --> 01:04.763
<i>This is Mavis McCready.</i>

01:04.765 --> 01:06.765
<i>If you're looking to book
Alonzo Ashbury,</i>

01:06.767 --> 01:09.201
<i>leave your name,
your venue, and a date.</i>

01:09.203 --> 01:11.103
<i>I'll get back to you.</i>

01:11.105 --> 01:13.272
<i>Anybody else, speak your
piece, keep it brief.</i>

01:13.274 --> 01:15.641
<i>Don't fill up my mailbox.</i>

01:15.643 --> 01:17.643
Mavis, it's Mae.

01:17.645 --> 01:21.313
We're gathering
at Moss Lake next Saturday

01:21.315 --> 01:24.183
at sunset
to scatter Robert's ashes.

01:24.185 --> 01:26.785
I thought you should know.

01:26.787 --> 01:30.589
James, myself, Jacob, Charity.

01:30.591 --> 01:33.659
I'm not asking Grace
for obvious reasons.

01:36.397 --> 01:41.567
Lord knows we have had
our distances, Mavis,

01:41.569 --> 01:42.801
in this family.

01:44.805 --> 01:46.805
Some earned,

01:46.807 --> 01:50.109
some given by God
for who knows why.

01:50.111 --> 01:53.779
II don't pretend to understand.

01:53.781 --> 01:56.648
This life is just
such a vale of tears.

01:56.650 --> 01:57.683
But...

02:00.688 --> 02:03.822
if there's any way that we...

02:03.824 --> 02:06.125
could make a new beginning,

02:06.127 --> 02:10.229
while there's still time
to make one...

02:10.231 --> 02:11.231
you and I...

02:15.569 --> 02:18.170
We'll be there at 5:00 PM.

